The Trenton in 1940, dwarfed by the 1924 Pacific Telephone and Telegraph Company Mutual Exchange, which has a giant &lt;a href=&quot;http://atcaonline.com/phone/we202.html&quot; title=&quot;withthee1&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;202 set&lt;/a&gt; on it.   On its other side, the &lt;a href=&quot;/wheresthemunny#comment-85&quot; title=&quot;trentatious&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Olive St. Bus Depot&lt;/a&gt; (414 S Grand behind that).  Poking up in the foreground, from Fifth and Hill, the &lt;a href=&quot;http://titleguaranteebuilding.com/history.php&quot; title=&quot;TG&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Title Guarantee&lt;/a&gt;. 
